## Commands the AI should reuse
- Build: `pnpm nx run automation-chrome-ext:build` (Vite, multi-entry).
- Watch/serve: `pnpm exec vite build --watch` (wired as `serve` target).
- Package ZIP: `pnpm nx build automation-chrome-ext && cd dist && zip -r ./automation-chrome-ext.zip .` (already in project targets).
- Copy static assets during build (manifest, popup/panel/options HTML/CSS, debug scripts): **preserve** the `cp` chain in the build step; add to it if new files are introduced.

> Output location is `apps/automation-chrome-ext/dist` with `background.js`, `content.js`, `popup.js`, `manifest.json`, `popup.html`, `chunks/`. Keep this contract stable.
